The paper describes a deep learning model that uses reinforcement learning to optimize its score in a game with incomplete and imperfect information. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to machine learning and game theory. 

cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper describes a deep neural network combined with Q-learning to optimize the agent's score. 

cs.GT (Game Theory) is also likely as the paper describes a game in which both players compete for ownership of a shared resource, and the model is trained to maximize the defender's time of ownership. 

cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another possible category as the paper describes a deep learning model that uses reinforcement learning. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is also possible as the paper describes a deep neural network. 

cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper describes a model that learns an optimal counter-strategy in a game with imperfect information.
